The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 September is 3,474 (402.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 September, there were 137 new confirmed cases (15.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 September, there were 118 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 16% (19 extra cases).
